cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DM, cs.FL, cs.CC 

The paper deals with the combinatorial generation and statistical properties of skeletons of lambda terms, which are related to logic and programming languages. The use of logic program transformations suggests a connection to logic and computation (cs.LO). The study of context-free grammars and the combinatorial generation of skeletons suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of statistical properties suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
